  16 Oct 2022; GitHub <noreply@github.com> gstreamer-player-1.1.2.ebuild:
  add missing pygobject dependency

  On a fresh install, gstreamer-player fails to load stating:
  ```
    File "/usr/lib/python3.10/site-packages/gsp/__init__.py", line 11, in
  <module>
      import gi  # pylint: disable=import-error
  ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'gi'
  ```

  This is caused by a missing dependency to pull in pygobject. Explicitly
  adding the dependency should solve the issue.

